<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1607,1850]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">
This species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[533,654,1607,1633]" name="Guatemala" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[671,821,1607,1634]" country="Guatemala" name="Alta Verapaz" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Alta Verapaz</collectingRegion>
) based on a single female. 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Giesbert, E. F." box="[1138,1436,1607,1634]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" refId="ref9556" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Giesbert, E. F. (1994) Checklist of the Cerambycidae and Disteniidae (Coleoptera) of the Western Hemisphere. Wolfsgarden Books, Burbank, 409 pp." type="book" year="1994">Monné &amp; Giesbert (1994)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[438,530,1644,1670]" name="Panama" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Panama</collectingCountry>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Turnbow, R. H. &amp; Cave, R. D. &amp; Thomas, M. C." box="[585,829,1643,1670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref10033" refString="Turnbow, R. H., Cave, R. D. &amp; Thomas, M. C. (2003) A list of the Cerambycidae of Honduras, with additions of previously unrecorded species. Ceiba, 44 (1), 1 - 43." type="journal article" year="2003">
Turnbow 
<emphasis box="[693,748,1644,1670]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
reported it from 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1129,1643,1669]" name="Honduras" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Honduras</collectingCountry>
.Apparently, the species appeared as occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[407,493,1679,1705]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[507,601,1680,1706]" country="Mexico" name="Yucatan" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Yucatán</collectingRegion>
) in 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Hovore, F. T." box="[644,928,1679,1706]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" refId="ref9594" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Hovore, F. T. (2005) Checklist of the Cerambycidae, or longhorned wood-boring beetles, of the Western Hemisphere. Bio Quip Publications, Rancho Dominguez, 393 pp." type="book" year="2005">Monné &amp; Hovore (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, but probably this record already was present in an early PDF version available online. The same regarding the new record from 
<collectingCountry box="[1070,1191,1715,1742]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="1" pageNumber="562">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
that also was listed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Hovore, F. T." box="[151,434,1751,1778]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" refId="ref9594" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Hovore, F. T. (2005) Checklist of the Cerambycidae, or longhorned wood-boring beetles, of the Western Hemisphere. Bio Quip Publications, Rancho Dominguez, 393 pp." type="book" year="2005">Monné &amp; Hovore (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, but we know that was already present in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hovore, F. T." box="[903,1072,1752,1778]" pageId="1" pageNumber="562" refId="ref9024" refString="Hovore, F. T. (2002) Longhorned Wood-boring beetles (Cerambycidae: Coleoptera) of Costa Rica. An annotated species list. Available at http: // www. bio-nica. info / biblioteca / Hovore 2002. pdf (accessed 17 June 2019)" type="url" year="2002">Hovore (2002)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
